<TITLE> Bad weather stops ferries </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Munshiganj, Apr 26 (bdnews24.com)  Ferries came to a halt at Mawa-ghat on Monday evening due to stormy weather. This has resulted in hundreds of vehicles waiting at the ghat. Md Ashikuzzaman, BIWTC's assistant general manager for Mawa-ghat, told bdnews24.com at 9pm that ferry services have become risky due to bad weather and stormy winds. "As a safety measure, all types of water vessels including the ferries in Mawa-Kaorakandi and Mawa-Mangalmajhi have been stopped," he added. He said three Ro-Ro ferries, loaded with cars and passengers, were waiting at the bank. The others were anchored. The official said that Ro-Ro ferries will resume by Monday night if the weather improves. bdnews24.co
